Program: Outlook
Title: Billy Leung on Changing the Law in Hong Kong
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbslf
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Billy Leung single-handedly changed Hong Kong's laws on same sex relationships. Also, listeners' memorable journeys. An eyewitness account of the military coup in Thailand. Australian aboriginal tribe granted ownership of the city of Perth. Tom Reynolds, the London Ambulance driver whose blog became a book. Finally, the story of Ota Benga, the Pgymy man kidnapped from Congo and put on display in USA. Presenter: Heather Payton. Show less